ACT:
 Article 235-District Courts and Courts Subordinate thereto-Control over vests in High Court-Power of Control comprises Appointment, Promotion and Imposition of Punishment in respect of Subordinate Judiciary-Decision to be arrived at after due enquiry-Governor to take action on recommendation of High Court.
 Fundamental Rules-FR 56(d) read subject to and in harmony with Article 235-Judicial officer-Compulsory retirement of- Decision to be taken by High Court-Governor to take action on recommendation of High Court.
 Civil Services-Action against Government servant.consists of two parts-First part is decision will have to be taken whether action is to be taken-Second part the decision to be carried out by a formal order.
 
